Bring a large pot of water to a boil. In a large skillet, cook garlic in olive oil for 1 to 2 minutes or until slightly yellow in color. Add carrots and saute for 4 to 5 minutes until lightly browned. Add the fennel and zucchini, season with salt and pepper and saute for about 3 minutes. Cook pasta according to package directions, drain and toss with the sauce. Remove from heat and add fresh marjoram and Parmigiano cheese. Stir to combine and serve.